## 🚀 Installation

### 1. Ubuntu Server Setup

```bash
# Update system packages
sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgrade -y
```

### 2. Wazuh Manager Installation (All-in-One)

```bash
# Download and execute Wazuh installation script
curl -sO https://packages.wazuh.com/4.9/wazuh-install.sh && sudo bash wazuh-install.sh -a -i
```

This installs:
- Wazuh Manager
- Wazuh Indexer (OpenSearch)
- Wazuh Dashboard

### 3. Verify Services

```bash
sudo systemctl status wazuh-manager
sudo systemctl status wazuh-indexer
sudo systemctl status wazuh-dashboard
```

### 4. Access Dashboard

Open a browser on Windows host and navigate to:
```
https://192.168.248.132
```
> Accept the self-signed certificate warning and log in with the credentials shown at the end of the installation script.

